{ 1.e4 e5 is called the Open Game or the Double King's Pawn Opening. This is by far the most popular reply at the 1600-level. We will immediately dive into the most important variations. Within the Open Game, we will most likely end up playing The Scotch Gambit covered in the first chapters. Alternatively, we could face the Petrov Defense, the Philidor Defense or the Latvian and Elephant Gambits. }
2. Nf3 { Developing and attacking the e5-pawn. } 2... Nf6
{ The Petrov Defense is on the board. This is usually a solid opening for Black. The Petrov has recently gained more popularity since Ian Nepomniatchi used it as the main repertoire in the 2021 World Championship Match against Magnus Carlsen. }
3. d4
