[Black "Caro-Kann #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c6
{ The Caro-Kann is closely related to the French opening, and Black prepares to strike back in the center on the second move by playing d5.  You can find here the variations for the Caro-Kann. }
2. d4
{ We love to get our pawns on e4 and d4 when Black doesn't prevent us from doing so. }
2... d5 3. e5
{ Like in the French Defense we are going for the Advance Variation. The idea is to prevent Black from developing freely and with e5 we take away the natural f6-square for Black's knight. }
3... c5 { Black is trying to counter in the center by attacking the d4-pawn. }
4. dxc5
{ We capture the pawn and challenge Black to win it back.   You will find the continuation of this variation here. }
