1. e4 d5
{ In the Scandinavian opening Black immediately attacks our e4-pawn. The Scandinavian is covered here. }
2. exd5 { We capture the pawn, forcing Black's queen to recapture. } 2... Nf6
{ Black is scared to bring out the queen early and tries to recapture the pawn with the knight. We don't protect the pawn and play d4. }
3. d4
{ Protecting the pawn with  3.Nc3  doesn't help since Black would still play  3...Nxd5  .   After  3.c4  Black will play  3...c6  when after  4.dxc6  Nxc6  Black's lead in development fully compensates for the pawn.  You will find the rest of this variation here. }
