[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Introduction & Quickstarter Guide"]
[Black "Scandinavian #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 d5
{ In the Scandinavian opening Black immediately attacks our e4-pawn. The Scandinavian is covered here. }
2. exd5 { We capture the pawn, forcing Black's queen to recapture. } 2... Qxd5
3. d4
{ This move is not so popular. Nevertheless, it is in my opinion the most tricky way to play against the Scandinavian.  After the main move  3.Nc3  we develop with tempo, however, the downside is that Black's queen moves to a safer square.  With 3.d4 we are putting our pawn in the center and wait for the perfect moment to target Black's queen. }
3... Nf6 4. Nf3
{ Developing and preparing to castle. We want to wait with attacking the queen until Black has played Nc6.   After  4...Nc6  we play  5.c4  attacking the queen  followed by d5, hunting the knight. You can find these variations here. }
