[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "1. Scotch Gambit: Main Line with 4...Nf6"]
[Black "Scotch Gambit: 4...Nf6 with 5...Ng4 #3"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 { Developing and attacking the e5-pawn. } 2... Nc6 3. d4
{ The Scotch Gambit has similarities to the Italian opening. Instead of playing the Italian with  3.Bc4  we first play the @@StartBracket@@usually@@EndBracket@@ temporary pawn sacrifice  3.d4  and only after  3...exd4  do we go for  4.Bc4  . }
3... exd4 4. Bc4
{ The Scotch Gambit has started. We play  4.Bc4  instead of  4.Nxd4  because we are going for quick development and castling.  Our bishop is already looking at the f7-square. White is now ready to castle; however, Black still needs to develop the knight and the bishop on the kingside to prepare to castle. }
4... Nf6
{ The best and most popular move. We now immediately put more pressure on our opponent by chasing away this knight. }
5. e5
{ Going for the knight hunt. It will be a signature move in our repertoire to hunt knights placed on f6 or c6. These squares are usually the best squares for Black's knights, and we will attack these knights mercilessly. }
5... Ng4
{ A logical move. Black is attacking the e5-pawn twice now, and we only have one defender. }
6. O-O
{ We use the rule of thumb and castle since the e5-pawn gets attacked. This indirectly protects the e5-pawn because we have the idea to create a pin along the e-file. }
6... Be7
{ Black is reinforcing the threat to capture on e5. After  6...Bc5  we reply with  7.c3  when the at the 1600-level most played  7...dxc3  8.Bxf7+  Kxf7  9.Ng5+  Kf8  10.Qxg4  White reaches a winning position.  If Black replies with   @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/pppp1ppp/2n5/2b1P3/2Bp2n1/2P2N2/PP3PPP/RNBQ1RK1 b kq - 0 7@@EndFEN@@  6...d5  7.Bb5  We pin the knight and have a comfortable position. }
7. Re1 { Defending the e5-pawn. } 7... d6
{ The only move Black can play to avoid a much worse position. } 8. exd6 Qxd6
9. b3 { Preparing an attack with Ba3. } 9... O-O 10. Ba3
{ After  10...Qd8  11.Bxe7  Nxe7  12.Nxd4  White regains the pawn. This is a solid variation for Black in which White only keeps a tiny advantage. }
*

