6... Ne4 7. Nxd4
{ We recapture the pawn and increase the pressure on the pinned knight. } 7...
Bc5
{ A tricky and strong move. Now  8.Nxc6  is dangerous because  8...Bxf2+  is possible. }
8. Be3 { We develop and defend the knight. } 8... Bd7 9. Bxc6
{ We need to eliminate the knight to prevent Black from capturing on d4, and we give Black doubled pawns. }
9... bxc6 10. O-O
{ White maintains nice attacking chances in this position! The attacking ideas are similar to the ones we will discuss in the main line later in this chapter. }
