11... Ne4 12. Be3
{ This is a nice development move that breaks the pin on the knight on d4.  If Black plays  12...Bb6  13.Nd2  c5  14.N4f3  Nxd2  15.Qxd2  d4  16.Bf2  we can play c3 at some point to exchange the pawn on d4, and we should also activate our rook on a1 to d1 or e1.   After  12...Qb8  we just go  13.b3  to prevent Black from  capturing the pawn on b2. }
