[White "5. Scotch Gambit: Sidelines"]
[Black "Scotch Gambit: 3...d5 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 { Developing and attacking the e5-pawn. } 2... Nc6 3. d4
{ The Scotch Gambit has similarities to the Italian opening. Instead of playing the Italian with  3.Bc4  we first play the @@StartBracket@@usually@@EndBracket@@ temporary pawn sacrifice  3.d4  and only after  3...exd4  do we go for  4.Bc4  . }
3... d5 { Black decided to create immediate chaos in the center! } 4. Nxe5
{ We capture the e5-pawn and also make sure that when Black captures on e4 our knight won't be under attack. }
4... Nxe5 5. dxe5 dxe4 6. Qxd8+
{ By trading queens we break Black's right to castle. } 6... Kxd8 7. Nc3
{ We are ready to pick up the e4-pawn. White has a significant advantage. White plans to castle long which immediately places the rook on the d-file, attacking Black's king. The bishops can come out to g5 and c4, targetting the king and the f7-pawn. Subsequently, the h1-rook can come to e1 and target the e4-pawn. }
*

