{ We capture the e5-pawn and also make sure that when Black captures on e4 our knight won't be under attack. }
4... dxe4 5. Bb5 { Pinning the knight. } 5... Bd7 6. Bxc6
{ We need to capture the knight because otherwise, Black will capture our knight and win a piece. It's best to capture with the bishop since after  6.Nxc6  bxc6  Black gains a tempo by attacking our bishop. }
6... Bxc6 7. O-O
{ We didn't play  7.Nxc6  breaking Black's pawn structure even though that would also be great for us. The reason is by not trading our knight, we prevent Black from playing @@StartFEN@@r2qkbnr/ppp2ppp/2b5/4N3/3Pp3/8/PPP2PPP/RNBQ1RK1 b kq - 1 7@@EndFEN@@  7...f5  defending the e4-pawn because we strike with  8.Qh5+  g6  9.Nxg6!    If Black doesn't play 7...f5 we will play Re1, capture the bishop, and win the e4-pawn! }
