{ A very sneaky move, opening up the position to attack with all our pieces. }
5... dxc3 6. Nxc3
{ The super attractive move  6.Qd5  threatening mate looks stronger than it is. After  6...Nh6  7.Bxh6  O-O  Black is suddenly threatening to capture the b2-pawn, trapping the rook as well as capturing the bishop.  After 6.Nxc3 our point is that Black still has difficulties developing the knight and isn't able to castle yet. }
6... d6 7. Qb3
{ Black has no good way to defend against Bxf7!  After  7...Na5  @@StartBracket@@attacking the queen and the bishop@@EndBracket@@  8.Bxf7+  Kf8  9.Qa4  Kxf7  10.Qxa5  White has a big advantage because of the better king safety.   If Black plays  7...Be6  we play  8.Bxe6  fxe6  9.Qxb7!!  and Black's position is collapsing. }
