[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 { Developing and attacking the e5-pawn. } 2... Nf6
{ The Petrov defense has started, this is usually a solid opening for Black. The Petrov has gained more popularity recently since Ian Nepomniatchi used it as the main repertoire in the 2021 World Championship match against Magnus Carlsen. }
3. d4
{ We play in a similar style as in the Scotch Gambit and start the fight in the center directly! I like this move a lot because it puts pressure on Black, and they have to make an important decision right away. }
3... Nxe4 4. dxe5
{ Making it impossible for the knight on e4 to go back to the safe f6 square. We can put pressure on Black's knight on e4. }
4... Bc5
{ This is a very principled and exciting move, Black is putting pressure on the f2 pawn; however, this is a risky way to play for Black. }
5. Bc4
{ Attack is the best defense, and we put pressure on the f7 pawn. And create a big threat with Qd5. }
5... Nxf2
{ This is the best move for Black, again we go for the counter-attack and also capture on f7 }
6. Bxf7+
{ This is a move we play more often in our repertoire. When the bishop is on c5, we immediately win back the piece. }
6... Kf8 { Black sidesteps with the queen. } 7. Qd5
{ Saving the queen and attacking the bishop. } 7... Nxh1 8. Bh5
{ Threatening mate! We don't play  8.Qxc5+  since Black plays  8...Kxf7  . }
8... Qe7 { Defending against the mate and protecting the bishop. } 9. Bg5
{ Attacking the queen. The queen doesn't have a safe square from where it can keep protecting the bishop. }
9... Bf2+ { Black gives an intermediate check to safe the bishop. } 10. Ke2
{ We want to open the first rank for our rook to pick up the knight. Also, we want to keep on attacking the bishop. }
10... Qe6 11. Nc3
{ Double attack. This move is beautiful! We are playing chess like a true master, using all our pieces on the board. Our rook attacks the knight, which is doomed. Also, we defended the queen. Soon we will collect the material, and White has a significant advantage. }
