1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d5
{ The Elephant Gambit, as the opening name already indicates, is a bit of a dubious opening. Still, we should be precise to punish Black for playing this move. Another dubious sideline Black could try is the Damiano Defence  2...f6  which we can punish with  3.Nxe5  when after  3...fxe5  4.Qh5+  Ke7  5.Qxe5+  Kf7  6.Bc4  d5  7.Bxd5+  Kg6  8.h4  White wins with a devastating attack. We plan to attack with h5 and after ...Kh6 go for d4+ when mate will follow soon. And after  8...h5  9.Bxb7  we will win the rook as Black's bishop should keep protecting the f5-square.   When after  2...f6  3.Nxe5  Black plays  3...Qe7  we should retreat with  4.Nf3  . Don't play  4.Qh5+  which would lose a piece after  5...g6  6.Nxg6  Qxe4+ }
3. exd5 { Forcing Black to bring out the queen. } 3... Qxd5 4. Nc3
{ Developing with tempo and White has a lead in development. After  4...Qc5  we can play  5.d4  and open all the lines.   If Black plays  4...Qe6  then we go  5.Bb5+  c6  6.Ba4  . White has a big lead in development, and after Black's knight hunting idea with  6...e4  we play  7.O-O  when after  7...exf3  8.Re1  is pinning and winning the queen. }
