[SetUp "1"]

{ What is the strongest continuation? } 1. Bc4
{ Again, we are attacking the f7-pawn. } 1... Bxf2+
{ Where should we move our king? } 2. Kf1
{ 2.Ke2  runs into the problem that after  2...Qe7  our king is weak on the e-file. After  3.Qd5  attacking the knight Black can defend with  3...f5  when after  4.exf6  we would lose our queen with  4...Nxf6  discovered check! }
2... O-O 3. Qd5
{ Attacking the knight and also the bishop is hanging. White is winning a piece. An alternative was  3.Bd5  . }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "10. Petrov, Philidor, Elephant & Latvian gambit Tactics"]
[Black "Exercise 6: Philidor Defense"]
