{ A very passive move. White is winning. This move has also been played frequently at the 1600-level. }
7. Qe2+
{ Usually, our queen is not well-placed on e2, since the queen is blocking our light-squared bishop, which hinders the development. In this case, we can justify playing Qe2+ since we force Black to play Qe7 as well, which hinders their dark-squared bishop from developing! }
7... Qe7 8. Be3
{ We are ready to play Nc3 and castle queenside. Black's king is stuck in the center, and we have a fantastic position. For Black not being able to develop the dark-squared bishop is problematic, since Black's king is many moves away from castling on either side. White can still aim for a queenside castle! }
