4... Nf6 5. Nc3
{ Here, the knight-hunting idea with  5.e5  wouldn't have worked since after  5...dxe5  6.dxe5  Qxd1+  @@StartBracket@@trading queens and breaking our right to castle@@EndBracket@@  7.Kxd1  Ng4!  attacks both the e5- and f2-pawns. Still, we keep in mind that later in the variation we will hunt the knight on f6 with e5! }
