1. e4 c5 2. c3
{ The Alapin variation starts. We prepare to play d4 next and make it possible to recapture with the pawn to create a strong center. It's our goal to get our pawns on e4 and d4! }
2... d6
{ Black's second most popular move at the 1600-level, which allows us to get a strong center. }
3. d4 cxd4
{ At the 1600-level this move is the overwhelming favorite. After the trade we can develop our knight to the most natural c3-square. }
4. cxd4
{ We are thrilled with White, as we have a strong center with our pawns on e4 and d4. }
4... Nf6 5. Nc3
{ Here, the knight-hunting idea with  5.e5  wouldn't have worked since after  5...dxe5  6.dxe5  Qxd1+  @@StartBracket@@trading queens and breaking our right to castle@@EndBracket@@  7.Kxd1  Ng4!  attacks both the e5- and f2-pawns. Still, we keep in mind that later in the variation we will hunt the knight on f6 with e5! }
5... g6 6. Nf3 Bg7 7. Bb5+
{ Developing with a check. Black has to block with a piece on d7, which means that subsequently, our knight-hunting idea becomes possible! }
