[Round "?"]
[White "13. Alapin Sicilian: Barmen Defense 2...d5"]
[Black "Alapin Sicilian: 2...d5 with 4...Nf6"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. c3 d5
{ This is one of the main variations for Black on the top-level called the Barmen's Defence. Black aims to strike back in the center immediately. At the 1600-level, the Barmen's Defense is way less popular and played in less than 10% of the Alapin games. }
3. exd5
{ We want to capture in the center, forcing Black to bring the queen out. }
3... Qxd5 4. d4
{ This position is a perfect illustration of why the Alapin is my recommendation. The bishops and the queen are free to develop quickly. We have set up an excellent base for our future development by throwing the center pawns forward. We will ensure that if Black makes one mistake, all our pieces are crushing through the opponent's position with lightning-fast development. Watch the model game where GM Mamedyarov won against GM Corrales Jimenez with a brilliant queen sacrifice. }
4... Nf6
{ Black wants to develop and prepare to go for a kingside castle. After  4...g6  5.Nf3  Bg7  we can develop the knight with  6.Na3  aiming to go Nb5-Nc7+ with a royal fork on the king and queen. After  6...cxd4  we can immediately play  7.Nb5  .  I won a nice game with this variation in my Banter Blitz session on chess24 on Friday 6th of May 2022. }
5. Nf3 { Developing and preparing to castle. } 5... Bg4
{ Black is pinning our knight and threatening to capture and give us doubled pawns. After  5...e6  we transpose to the model game from Mamedyarov-Corrales where we can continue with  6.Na3  cxd4  7.Nb5  threatening a royal fork with Nc7+. }
6. Be2 { Preparing to castle and defending the knight. } 6... e6 7. h3
{ Provoking the bishop to make a favorable trade for us. Black shouldn't accept the trade and play  7...Bh5  . The game could continue with  8.O-O  Nc6  9.Be3  White threatens to capture on c5 and after  9...cxd4  10.cxd4  White plans to develop with  Nc3  and subsequently can play  Qb3  ,  Rd1  , and  d5  trading the isolated pawn and getting a strong initiative . }
*

[Event "?"]
