[SetUp "1"]

{ What is the strongest continuation here? } 1. Bb5+
{ Developing with check. Black is forced to block with a piece on d7, which means that subsequently, our knight-hunting idea becomes possible! It's important to note that the signature knight-hunting move  1.e5  is too early here, since after  1...dxe5  2.dxe5  Qxd1+  White either has to retreat the knight to a passive position or break the right to castle. }
1... Bd7
{ Black's light-squared bishop blocks the d-file, which makes it possible to go for the knight-hunt immediately. }
2. e5 { Going for our signature knight-hunting move. } 2... Bxb5
{ A big blunder. We are winning a piece! Yet, this is the most popular move at the 1600-level. }
3. exf6 { A double attack and White wins a piece. } 3... Bxf6 4. Nxb5 Qa5+
{ Black tries to strike back with a double attack. } 5. Nc3
{ We save our knight and have a winning position. } *

