1. e4 e6
{ The French 1.e4 e6 is the third most popular move at the 1600-level. } 2. d4
{ Just like in the Alapin, we love to get our pawn on e4 and d4. With both pawns in the center, we can develop both the bishops and the queen whenever we want, as well as go for our knight-hunting ideas. }
2... c5 3. d5 { We immediately grab more space in the center. } 3... exd5 4.
exd5 d6 5. Nf3
{ Developing the knight. We are ready to play c4, develop the light-squared bishop and castle. Black's dark-squared bishop is blocked by the d6-pawn, and Black's knight cannot develop to the most natural c6-square. }
