e5
{ We go for the Advance Variation in the French. When we play e5, Black's light-squared bishop is locked in by Black's pawn chain. Also, Black's knight can no longer develop to the most natural f6-square. }
3... c5
{ Black wants to attack and exchange the d4-pawn. If that happens, our e5-pawn would become weak. That's why we should defend this pawn. }
