{ It would be a mistake to play  5.b4  defending the pawn since after  5...a5  @@StartBracket@@undermining our b4-pawn@@EndBracket@@  6.c3  axb4  7.cxb4  b6  @@StartBracket@@threatening to win the c5-pawn@@EndBracket@@  8.cxb6  Bxb4+  9.Bd2  Qxb6  Black has a better position. }
5... Bxc5 6. Bd3
{ We are ready to castle! Also, we can play a3, b4, and Bb2, gaining a tempo on Black's dark-squared bishop and developing. }
