1. e4 d5
{ In the Scandinavian opening, Black immediately attacks our e4-pawn. } 2. exd5
{ We capture the pawn, forcing Black's queen to recapture. } 2... Qxd5 3. d4
{ This move is not so popular. Nevertheless, it is, in my opinion, the most tricky way to play against the Scandinavian. We develop with tempo after the main move  3.Nc3  ;  (however, the downside is that Black's queen moves to a safer square.)   With  3.d4  , we put our pawn in the center and wait for the perfect moment to target Black's queen. After  3...c6  or  3...Qd8  , we continue with  4.Nf3  and plan to continue development with Be2, O-O, c4, Nc3. }
3... Nc6
{ Black's main move and most logical move. Black is targetting our d4-pawn. We are happy to see the knight on c6 because, as we already learned in the Alapin, we can go knight-hunting and play d5 after we have managed to chase away Black's queen. First, we should develop and defend the d4-pawn. }
4. Nf3
{ We develop and defend in the center. We are ready for our knight-hunting plan to attack the queen with either c4 or Nc3 and subsequently, after the queen moves, play d5 hunting the knight. At this point, Black is in a tough spot, and they have to play multiple good moves to get a playable position. }
4... Bg4
{ Developing and counterattacking by pinning our knight. If  4...e5  , we play the strong  5.Nc3  developing and attacking the queen and after  5...Bb4  6.Bd2  Bxc3  7.Bxc3  White threatens to capture on e5 and has a better position. }
5. Nc3
{ Developing and attacking the queen. This position is the same as in the Alapin Barmen Defense when the c-pawns are still on the board. When Black's queen moves, we plan to continue with d5, hunting the knight! }
5... Qe6+
{ The most popular move at the 1600-level and a big mistake. The queen is misplaced here, blocking the e7-pawn, which makes Black unable to develop the dark-squared bishop. }
6. Be3
{ We don't play  6.Be2  since after  6...Bxf3  Black weakens our pawn structure, and we must recapture with  7.gxf3  . }
6... Bxf3 7. Qxf3 Nxd4
{ The most popular move at the 1600-level. White is winning now. } 8. Qxb7
{ An essential attacking move and the only good move. After  8...Nxc2  9.Kd2  , we are attacking the rook and the knight. The computer gives  +10.   After  8...Rd8  9.O-O-O  brings our king to safety and attacks the knight. White is also winning, and the computer gives  +9. }
