{ White has a big lead in development and is ready to castle next move. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "22. Pirc, Modern, Alekhine and Owen's Defense "]
[Black "Alekhine's Defense: 1...Nf6"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nf6 { The Alekhine opening. Black attacks the e4-pawn immediately. } 2.
e5 { Our signature knight-hunting move. } 2... Nd5 3. d4
{ We create our big center and are ready to develop all the pieces. } 3... d6
4. c4 { Attacking the knight and gaining a stronger center. } 4... Nb6 5. f4
{ We ensure our big pawn center by defending the e5-pawn. } 5... dxe5 6. fxe5
{ We don't play  6.dxe5  since after  6...Qxd1  7.Kxd1  we lose our right to castle. }
6... Nc6 { Black develops and attacks the d4-pawn. } 7. Be3
{ This is an important moment. Black attacks the d4-pawn and we don't want to defend with  7.Nf3  since  7...Bg4  is pinning the knight and Black keeps the pressure on our center.  With  7.Be3  we keep our strong pawns in the center, giving White an advantage. }
7... Bf5 8. Nc3
{ Still, we would like to postpone  8.Nf3  since it runs into  8...Bg4  pinning the knight. That's why we first develop the knight on the queenside. }
8... e6 9. Be2
{ White is ready to play Nf3 and castle. We have a significant advantage because of the strong pawn center. Check out how I won my game from this position in the model game. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "22. Pirc, Modern, Alekhine and Owen's Defense "]
[Black "Owen's Defense: 1...b6 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 b6
{ Owen's Defense. Famous streamer Levy Rozman made a video recommending this opening. }
2. d4 { We gladly take the opportunity to get a strong center. } 2... Bb7
{ Black develops and attacks the e4-pawn. } 3. Bd3
{ It is better not to play  3.Nc3  since after  3...e6  4.Nf3  Bb4  Black pins our knight and threatens to capture the e4-pawn. }
3... Nf6 4. Qe2
{ Again we don't want to play  4.Nc3  to avoid getting pinned.  This time our typical knight-hunting move  4.e5  would run into  4...Bxg2!  and we lose the rook. }
4... Nc6 5. c3
{ This move supports our center and also keeps Black from playing Nb4. White is ready to play Nf3 and castle. Also, we are ready to start hunting the knight with e5! }
*

