[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "23. Theme-based Tactic Drills "]
[Black "Exercise 1: Scotch Gambit 4...Nf6 "]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bqkb1r/pppp1ppp/2n5/4n3/2Bp4/5N2/PPP2PPP/RNBQ1RK1 w kq - 0 7"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ Can you find White's most powerful move? } 7. Nxe5
{ Capturing is always the first thing to consider! With a capture, we are gaining a material advantage, forcing our opponent to recapture, making it possible to calculate exactly how the game will continue.  Another candidate move would be  7.Re1  ; this doesn't work because after  7...d6  , we would love to play f4 attacking the pinned knight. However, our knight on f3 is preventing us from playing this move. After  8.Nxe5  Black will play  8...dxe5  . }
7... Nxe5 8. Re1 { Pinning the knight! } 8... d6 9. f4
{ Attacking a pinned piece is a nice way to gain material! The knight cannot move, so it's lost. }
9... Bg4 { Black is counterattacking our queen. What to do now? } 10. Qxg4
{ Thank you very much! Since we pin the knight, we can capture the bishop for free. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "23. Theme-based Tactic Drills "]
[Black "Exercise 2: Scotch Gambit sidelines"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1b1k1nr/pppp1ppp/5q2/2b1n3/2Bp4/5N2/PPP2PPP/RNBQ1RK1 w kq - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ What is White's best continuation? } 1. Nxe5
{ Trading the knights to be able to pin the queen. We don't want to play  1.Re1  immediately since Black can defend with  1...d6  . }
1... Qxe5 2. Re1 { Pinning and winning the queen. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "23. Theme-based Tactic Drills "]
[Black "Exercise 3: Scotch Gambit sidelines"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bqkb1r/pppp1pp1/2n4p/4P3/2Bp2n1/5N2/PPP2PPP/RNBQ1RK1 w kq - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ How does White gain a winning advantage? } 1. h3
{ We learned that the knight could not capture on e5, so let's force the knight to do that! }
1... Ngxe5
{ One trick we should watch out for is that after  1...h5  2.hxg4  hxg4  Black  wants to play Qh4 and Qh1 mate after we move our knight! We play  3.Ng5!  blocking the queen and White has a completely winning position. }
2. Nxe5
{ 2.Re1  immediately wouldn't work because Black can defend with  2...d6  . }
2... Nxe5 3. Re1 { Pinning the knight. } 3... d6 4. f4
{ Adding another attacker to make sure we will win the knight. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "23. Theme-based Tactic Drills "]
[Black "Exercise 4: Scotch Gambit 4...Nf6 "]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1b1kb1r/pppp1ppp/2q5/5P2/2Bpn1P1/8/PPP4P/RNBQR1K1 w kq - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ How do we take advantage of Black's pinned knight? } 1. Qd3
{ Right now, we attack the pinned knight on e4, and we play Rxe4 on the next move. Also, we set up a new trap when Black would defend with d5.   Don't forget that after  1.Qxd4  Bc5  we would lose the queen. }
1... d5 2. Bb5
{ We could not win the knight anymore; however, we pin and win the queen, which is even better! White is completely winning now. }
*

