[SetUp "1"]

{ Black copies our strategy and goes for a knight-hunt! How should we cope with that? }
4. Qe2 { Pinning the e4-pawn. } 4... Nf6
{ After  4...Qf6  5.Nc3  develops with tempo and wins the e4-pawn. } 5. d3
{ Attacking the pinned e4-pawn again and opening the diagonal for the bishop. }
5... Qxd5 6. Nc3 { Developing and attacking the queen and the e4-pawn. } 6...
Bb4 { Developing and pinning the knight. } 7. Nd2
{ A brilliant move, unpinning the knight to reinforce the threat to capture the queen and adding another attacker to the e4-pawn. White is winning the e4-pawn and has a big advantage. }
*

