[SetUp "1"]

{ What typical motif do we have here? } 1. d5
{ Our signature knight-hunting move. } 1... exd5 2. exd5 Nb8 3. Qe2+
{ Usually, our queen is not well-placed since it blocks our light-squared bishop, which hinders the development. In this case, we can justify playing Qe2+ since we force Black to play Qe7 too, which prevents their dark-squared bishop from developing! }
3... Be7 { Black falls for our trap. } 4. d6
{ Pinning and winning the bishop. } *

