[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "23. Theme-based Tactic Drills "]
[Black "Exercise 9: Philidor Defense"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bqkbnr/pppn1pp1/7p/4p3/2B1P3/5N2/PPP2PPP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 0 6"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ How can we start a dangerous attack? } 6. Bxf7+
{ We strike, and White has a winning position! Usually, a piece sacrifice on f7 is not strong enough once we don't have a follow-up tactic to win back more material. In this position, we have a lovely tactic on the next move. }
6... Kxf7 7. Nxe5+
{ A deadly strike! Black's knight is pinned, so cannot capture. At the 1600-level, the most popular move is  7...Ke8  when  8.Qh5+  already leads to a forced mate. When Black plays  7...Kf6  White wins after  8.Nc3  Kxe5  9.Qd5+  Kf6  10.Qf5+  Ke7  11.Nd5+  Kd6  12.Bf4+  White has a devasting attack hunting Black's king with all forces, and mate should follow soon. }
*

