[SetUp "1"]

{ Do you know the famous Greek gift tactic? } 9. Bxh7+
{ This idea is known as the Greek gift. When Black captures the bishop, we have a famous checkmating idea }
9... Kxh7 10. Ng5+ Kg8
{ After  10...Kg6  many moves are winning, the most convincing is  11.h4  which threatens h5+ and subsequently when Black has to play Kh6, we can win the queen with a discovered check by playing Nxf7+. }
11. Qh5
{ The idea is to play Qh7 mate on the next move. After  11...Re8  12.Qh7+  Kf8  13.Qh8+  Ng8  14.Nh7+  Ke7  15.Bg5+  White is winning. Black doesn't have any good moves; after  15...Nf6  we play  16.Qxg7  we will win the knight next and have a devastating attack. }
