{ How would you proceed in this position? } 1. e5
{ Our signature knight-hunting move. } 1... Ng4 2. Qd5
{ Threatening Qxf7 mate. This move is important because we are also defending the e5-pawn, which Black attacks twice.   In this position, our idea with  2.O-O  doesn't work since after  2...Ngxe5  3.Nxe5  Nxe5  4.Re1  doesn't pin the knight because Black's bishop blocks the e-file. }
2... O-O 3. h3 { Chasing the knight to the edge of the board! } 3... Nh6 4.
Bxh6
{ Weakening the pawn structure in front of Black's king. After  4...gxh6  I recommend  5.Qe4  threatening Bd3 and Qxh7 mate. }
