[SetUp "1"]

{ Find the best continuation for White. } 1. e5
{ Our signature move, hunting Black's knight. } 1... Ng4 2. h3
{ A knight on the rim is dim! So let's make the knight move to this poor square. }
2... Nh6 3. Bg5
{ Before taking the knight, we force Black's dark-squared bishop to go to e7. }
3... Be7 4. Bxh6
{ Weakening Black's pawn structure, and also Black's king safety as Black planned to castle kingside. }
4... gxh6
{ We are happy that we forced Black's dark-squared bishop to go to e7. The bishop would be stronger on f8 since then it could go to g7 to replace the missing pawn. }
5. Qxd4
{ Developing the queen. Keeping firm control in the center and preparing to castle long. After  5...Nc6  we play  6.Qe3  attacking the h6-pawn. }
