[White "24. Model Games"]
[Black "Viswanathan Anand vs. Jan Krzysztof Duda, Paris 2019"]
[Result "*"]

{ Let's now look at the blitz game between the 5-time world Champion Anand @@StartBracket@@rated 2764@@EndBracket@@ and the winner of the 2021 world cup Duda @@StartBracket@@rated 2729@@EndBracket@@. }
1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. d4 Nf6 4. Nf3 Bg4 5. Be2
{ The 5-time world champion decides to use mytricky recommendation against the Scandinavian. }
5... e6 6. h3 Bh5 7. O-O
{ As you see, Anand keeps on delaying the attack on the queen until Black has played Nc6. Duda doesn't fall for the trap. }
7... Be7 8. c4
{ Only after developing the entire kingside, does Anand decide to chase away the queen. }
8... Qd8 9. Qb3
{ Attacking the b7-pawn. The best cloud engine already give an opening advantage of +1.5 for White, which is a stunning advantage for top-level chess after just nine moves. }
9... Qc8 10. Nc3 O-O 11. Be3 Nbd7 12. Rfd1 h6 13. Rac1
{ White has a big lead in development. Even though the advantage is big for White, Duda still managed to get a solid position. The game had some ups and downs, which is logical for a blitz game but Anand managed to win! }
13... a6 14. a3 Re8 15. Qc2 Bg6 16. Bd3 Bxd3 17. Rxd3 b6 18. Ne5 Nxe5 19. dxe5
Nd7 20. Bf4 Nf8 21. Rg3 Kh8 22. Re1 Ng6 23. Bc1 Qb7 24. Rxg6
{ A brilliant rook sacrífice. } 24... fxg6 25. Qxg6 Bf8 26. Ne4 c5 27. Bf4 Rad8
28. Nd6 Bxd6 29. exd6 Rf8 30. Be5 Kg8 31. Re4 Rf5 32. Qxe6+ Qf7 33. Qxf7+ Rxf7
34. f4 g5 35. g3 Kh7 36. Kf2 gxf4 37. gxf4 Kg6 38. Kf3 Kf5 39. Re1 Rg8 40. Rd1
Rd7 41. Rd5 Ke6
{ I suspect that Duda lost on time here, but Anand has a much better position. }
