[Result "*"]

{ Also strong player fall for the opening tricks in the course. As the variations are so tricky for Black I love to play them in bullet and blitz games. The is a bullet game with only 1 minute each where I played on lichess against GaWegMan @@StartBracket@@2473@@EndBracket@@. }
1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. dxc5 Nc6 5. Nf3 Bg4 6. c3 e6 7. Be3 Nxe5 8. Qa4+
Qd7 9. Bb5 { Pinning the queen and forcing the knight back to c6. } 9... Nc6
10. Qxg4
{ The course covered everything this variation here White is already a piece up and has a winning position. }
10... Nf6 11. Qa4
{ The queen goes back to add more pressure on the pinned knight. } 11... Be7
12. Ne5 { The knight is still pinned so I add anther attacker. } 12... Qc7 13.
Nxc6 bxc6 14. Bxc6+ { Black is getting destroyed here. } 14... Kf8 15. Bxa8
{ In a game with a regular time control Black would already resign here. Since we were playing bullet and had both 30 seconds left my opponent still played on for a bit. }
15... g6 16. Nd2 Kg7 17. Bc6 Rc8 18. Bb5 Ng4 19. Qxg4
{ Oepsiee Black blundered another piece. } 19... h5 20. Qa4 Bf6 21. O-O e5 22.
Rfe1 Rd8 23. Nb3 Qe7 24. Rad1 h4 25. Bc6 h3 26. g3 Qf8 27. Bxd5 Qh8 28. Qe4 Qh5
29. c6 Rc8 30. Nc5 Be7 31. Nd7 Bd6 32. c4 f5 33. Qd3 e4 34. Qd4+ Kh7 35. Nf6+
{ Forking and winning the queen as well. It's nice to see that the opening tricks also work against high rated opponents, even though I am sure my opponent would have played better with more time on the clock. }
